field_paragraph_text.value:
A SWOT Analysis is an analysis where you identify internal and external factors that could affect the success of your project.  This type of analysis helps you understand:

  • Strengths: What your project or team can do well.
  • Weaknesses: What your project or team need help with.
  • Opportunities: What is happening in your community or networks that could help your project.
  • Threats: What is happening in your community or country that could make it harder to do your project.

Doing a SWOT analysis will help you know what steps you will need to take to make your project a success, what challenges you may have trying to do your project, ideas for how to overcome challenges, and resources that might help you do your project. It is a good idea to discuss these questions with the people involved in the project.
